export const loadedDocumentHtml = "<ol><li><strong>Introduction</strong></li></ol><h1>Innovate UK Business Connect PRE-QUALIFICATION QUESTIONNAIRE</h1><p>This Pre-Qualification Questionnaire (“PQQ”) has been issued by Innovate UK Business Connect in connection with a competitive procurement for the provision of services set out in the Innovate UK Business Connect Digital Services Framework.</p><ol><li><strong>Notes for completion</strong></li></ol><p>Please answer every question in English. Many procurements generate a great deal of interest from Potential Providers, so please ensure that you complete the questionnaire as requested. Failure to do so may result in your application being disqualified. If the question does not apply to you, please write N/A; if you don’t know the answer please write N/K.</p><p>“We” or “Authority” means Innovate UK Business Connect.</p><p>“You” or “Your” or the “Potential Provider” means the business or company</p><p>which is completing this PQQ.</p><p>Where you have a valid reason for being unable to provide the specific information requested in relation to this procurement, other information may be accepted but only if it is considered appropriate by the Authority.</p><p>You must inform the Authority of any material changes to the information provided by the PQQ as soon as you become aware of the change.</p><ol><li><strong>Return of this PQQ</strong></li></ol><p>Please return this form not later than 16th May 2025 to: <a href=\"mailto:mike.snow@iukbc.org\">mike.snow@iukbc.org</a></p><p>In your response, you must provide the name, position, and contact detail for the person within the business or company of the Potential Provider responsible for this requirement in Part 1 - Form A.</p><ol><li><strong>Contact point within the Authority for all queries</strong></li></ol><p>E-mail: <a href=\"mailto:mike.snow@iukbc.org\">mike.snow@iukbc.org</a></p><ol><li><strong>Verification of Information Provided</strong></li></ol><p>The higher the risk of the procurement, the higher the level of verification is likely to be required. Not all questions require supporting documents up front at this stage (for example certificates, statements with this questionnaire.) <strong>However, the Authority may ask to see these documents at a later stage, so it is advisable you ensure they can be made available upon request. </strong>You may also be asked to clarify your answers or provide more details about certain issues.</p><ol><li><strong>Sub-Contracting Arrangements</strong></li></ol><p>Where a sub-contracting approach is proposed, all information requested should be given in respect of the prime contractor.</p><p>Where sub-contractors will play a significant role in the delivery of goods or services, or both, under any ensuing contract, please indicate in a separate annex (by inserting the relevant company/organisation name) the composition of the supply chain, indicating which member of the supply chain will be responsible for the elements of the requirement.</p><p>It is recognised that arrangements in relation to sub-contracting may be subject to future change. However, Potential Providers should be aware that where sub-contractors are to play a significant role, any changes to those sub-contracting arrangements may constitute a material change and therefore may affect the ability of the Potential Provider to proceed with the procurement process or to provide the goods or services, or both.</p><ol><li><strong>Consortia Arrangements</strong></li></ol><p>If the Potential Provider is bidding for the requirement as a consortium, the following information must be provided:</p><ul><li><ul><li>full details of the consortium; and</li><li>the information sought in this PQQ in respect of each of the consortium’s</li></ul></li></ul><p>constituent members as part of a single composite response.</p><p>Potential Providers should provide details of the actual or proposed percentage shareholding of the constituent members within the consortium in a separate Annex. If a consortium is not proposing to form a corporate entity, full details of alternative proposed arrangements should be provided in the Annex. However, please note the Authority reserves the right to require a successful consortium to form a single legal entity in accordance with Regulation 2 of the Public Contracts Regulations 2015 (where applicable).</p><p>The Authority recognises that arrangements in relation to consortia may (within limits) be subject to future change. Potential Providers should therefore respond in the light of the arrangements as currently envisaged. Potential Providers are reminded that any future proposed change in relation to consortia must be notified to the Authority so that it can make a further assessment by applying the selection criteria to the new information provided.</p><ol><li><strong>Anti-Competitive Behaviour</strong></li></ol><p>The Authority is required by Regulation of the Public Contracts Regulations 2015 to ensure that all Potential Providers are treated equally and in a non-discriminatory way during the procurement process. The Authority therefore needs to prohibit anti- competitive behaviour to ensure a fair and non-discriminatory procurement process. You are required to report any final convictions or settlements with regard to anti- competitive behaviour (and any measures that you have taken to prevent such</p><p>behaviour happening again) in your response to the appropriate question(s) in Forms B and C (depending on the nature of the conviction or settlement).</p><p>If the Authority suspects anti-competitive behaviour, the Authority will require evidence from you that your arrangements are not anti-competitive. Any evidence of any anti- competitive behaviour in relation to this procurement could result in you being disqualified from the procurement process.</p><ol><li><strong>Selection of Tenderers</strong></li></ol><p>During the PQQ stage, the intention is to arrive at a Short List up to 6 qualified Potential Providers for formal invitation to tender against the requirement as advertised.</p><p>References, site visits or demonstrations or presentations are unlikely to be requested at this stage, but the Authority reserves the right to request them as a part of the PQQ process.</p><p>The Authority will contact you again by week commencing 27th May 2025 to let you know whether you have been successful. If so, you will then be invited to tender for the contract.</p><ol><li><strong>Miscellaneous</strong></li></ol><p>Under no circumstances shall the Authority incur any liability in respect of this PQQ or any supporting documentation. The Authority will not reimburse any costs incurred by Potential Providers in connection with preparation and submission of their responses to this PQQ.</p><p><a id=\"PART_1:_FORM_A:_Organisation_and_Contact\"></a> PART 1: FORM A: Organisation and Contact Details\t</p><table><tr><td><p>Full name of organisation tendering (or of organisation acting as lead contact where a consortium bid is being</p><p>submitted)</p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>Pixel Fusion Ltd.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"3\"><p><strong>ORGANISATION DETAILS</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Registered office address</p></td><td><p>Company or charity registration</p><p>number</p></td><td><p>14585902</p></td></tr><tr><td></td><td><p>VAT registration</p><p>number</p></td><td><p>GB449537064</p></td></tr><tr><td></td><td><p>Name of immediate parent</p><p>company</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td></tr><tr><td></td><td><p>Name of ultimate</p><p>parent company</p></td><td><p>n/a</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"><p>Type of organisation</p></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p>i) a public limited co.</p></td><td></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"><p>Limited Company</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p>ii) a limited company</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p>iii) a limited liability partnership</p></td></tr><tr><td></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p>iii) other partnership</p></td><td></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"3\"></td></tr><tr><td></td><td><p>iv) sole trader</p></td></tr><tr><td></td><td><p>v) other (please specify)</p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><strong>CONTACT DETAILS</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p>Contact details for enquiries about this PQQ</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Name</p></td><td><p>Gareth Heggie, Director</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Address</p></td><td><p>Office 10 The Hive, Grimsby, DN31 1EP, UK</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Post Code</p></td><td><p>DN31 1EP</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Country</p></td><td><p>England</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Phone</p></td><td><p>0330 133 2536</p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td><p>Mobile</p></td><td><p>Mobile: +44 7531 052349</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Email</p></td><td><p>gareth@pixel-fusion.com</p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"3\"><p>Consortia and Sub-Contracting</p></td><td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"3\"><ol><li>Your organisation is bidding to provide the services required itself.</li><li>Your organisation is bidding in the role of Prime Contractor and intends to use third parties to provide some services.</li><li>The Potential Provider is a consortium</li></ol></td><td><p>X</p></td></tr><tr><td></td></tr><tr><td></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><p>If your answer is (b) or (c) please indicate in a separate annex (by inserting the relevant company/organisation name) the composition of the supply chain, indicating which member of the supply chain (which may include the Potential Provider solely or together with other providers) will be responsible for the elements of the requirement.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><p><strong>QUESTIONS 1.1 and 1.2 FOR COMPLETION BY NON-UK BUSINESSES ONLY</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1.1</p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>Registration with professional body</p><p>Is your business registered with the appropriate trade or professional register(s) in the EU member state where it is established (as set out in <strong><em>Annexes IX A-C of Directive 2004/18/EC</em></strong>) under the conditions laid down by that member state).</p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>n/a</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1.2</p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>Is it a legal requirement in the State where you are established for you to be licensed or a member of a relevant organisation in order to provide the requirement in this procurement? If yes, please provide details of what is required and confirm that you have complied with this.</p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>n/a</p></td></tr></table><p><a id=\"PART_1:_FORM_B_-_Grounds_for_mandatory_r\"></a> PART 1: FORM B - Grounds for mandatory rejection\t</p><h1>Important Notice:</h1><p><strong>In some circumstances the Authority is required by law to exclude you from participating further in this procurement. If you answer ‘yes’ to any question in this section it is very unlikely that your application will be accepted. If you answer “yes”, please set out (in a separate Annex) full details of the relevant conviction and any remedial action taken subsequently.</strong></p><p>Please state ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ to each question.</p><table><tr><td></td><td><p><strong>Answer</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><strong>Has your organisation or any directors or partner or any other person who has powers of representation, decision or control been convicted of any of the following offences?</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(a)  conspiracy within the meaning of section 1 or 1a of the Criminal Law Act 1977 or article 9 or 9a of the Criminal Attempts and Conspiracy (Northern Ireland) Order 1983 where that conspiracy relates to participation in a criminal organisation as defined in Article 2 of Council Framework Decision 2008/841/JHA;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(b)  corruption within the meaning of section 1 of the Public Bodies Corrupt Practices Act 1889 or section 1 of the Prevention of Corruption Act 1906 (as amended); where the offence relates to active corruption</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(c) the offence of bribery, where the offence relates to active corruption; the offence of bribery within the meaning of section 1 or 6 of the Bribery Act 2010;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(d)  fraud, where the offence relates to fraud affecting the financial interests of the European Communities as defined by Article 1 of the Convention relating to the protection of the financial interests of the European Union, within the meaning of:</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(i)\tthe offence of cheating the Revenue;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(ii)\tthe offence of conspiracy to defraud;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(iii)  fraud or theft within the meaning of the Theft Act 1968, the Theft Act (Northern Ireland) 1969, the Theft Act 1978 or the Theft (Northern Ireland) Order 1978;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(iv)  fraudulent trading within the meaning of section 458 of the Companies Act 1985, article 451 of the Companies (Northern Ireland) Order 1986 or section 993 of the Companies Act 2006;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td><p>(v)  defrauding the Customs within the meaning of section 170 of the Customs and Excise Management Act 1979 or section 72 of the Value Added Tax Act 1994;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(vi)  an offence in connection with taxation in the European Community within the meaning of section 71 of the Criminal Justice Act 1993; or</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(vii) destroying, defacing or concealing of documents or procuring the extension of a valuable security within the meaning of section 20 of the Theft Act 1968 or section 9 of the Theft Act (Northern Ireland) 1969;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(viii)\tfraud within the meaning of section 2, 3 or 4 of the Fraud Act 2006; or</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(ix)  making, adapting, supplying, or offering to supply articles for use in frauds within the meaning of Section 7 of the Fraud Act 2006;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(e)\tmoney laundering within the meaning of section 340(11) of the Proceeds of Crime Act 2002;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(f)\tan offence in connection with the proceeds of criminal conduct within the meaning of section 93A, 93B or 93C of the Criminal Justice Act 1988 or article 45, 46, or 47 of the Proceeds of Crime (Northern Ireland) Order 1996; or</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(g)  an offence in connection with the proceeds of drug trafficking within the meaning of section 49, 50 or 51 of the Drug Trafficking Act 1994; or</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(h)  any other offence within the meaning of Article 45(1) of Directive 2004/18/EC as defined by the national law of any relevant State.</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr></table><p><a id=\"PART_1:_FORM_C_-_Grounds_for_discretiona\"></a> PART 1: FORM C - Grounds for discretionary rejection\t</p><h1>Important Notice:</h1><p><strong>The Authority is entitled to exclude you from consideration if any of the following apply but may decide to allow you to proceed further. If you cannot answer ‘no’ to every question it is possible that your application might not be accepted. In the event that any of the following do apply, please set out (in a separate Annex) full details of the relevant incident and any remedial action taken subsequently. The information provided will be taken into account by the Authority in considering whether or not you will be able to proceed any further in respect of this procurement exercise.</strong></p><p>Please state ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ to each question.</p><table><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><strong>Is any of the following true of your organisation?</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(a) being an individual,</p><p>is a person in respect of whom a debt relief order has been made, is bankrupt or has had a receiving order or administration order or bankruptcy restrictions order, or a debt relief restrictions order made against him or has made any composition or arrangement with or for the benefit of his creditors or has not made any conveyance or assignment for the benefit of his creditors or appears unable to pay or to have no reasonable prospect of being able to pay, a debt within the meaning of section 268 of the Insolvency Act 1986, or article 242 of the Insolvency (Northern Ireland) Order 1989, or in Scotland has granted a trust deed for creditors or become otherwise apparently insolvent, or is the subject of a petition presented for sequestration of his estate, or is the subject of any similar procedure under the law of</p><p>any other state;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(b) being a partnership constituted under Scots law,</p><p>has granted a trust deed or become otherwise apparently insolvent, or is the subject of a petition presented for sequestration of its estate;</p><p>or</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(c) being a company or any other entity within the meaning of section 255 of the Enterprise Act 2002</p><p>has passed a resolution or is the subject of an order by the court for the company’s winding up otherwise than for the purpose of bona fide reconstruction or amalgamation, or had a receiver, manager or administrator on behalf of a creditor appointed in respect of the company’s business or any part thereof or is the subject of similar</p><p>procedures under the law of any other state?</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><strong>Has your organisation</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(a) been convicted of a criminal offence relating to the conduct of your business or profession;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(b) committed an act of grave misconduct in the course of your</p><p>business or profession;</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(c) failed to fulfil obligations relating to the payment of social security</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td><p>contributions under the law of any part of the United Kingdom or of the relevant State in which you are established;</p></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><p>(d) failed to fulfil obligations relating to the payment of taxes under the</p><p>law of any part of the United Kingdom or of the relevant State in which you are established; or</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>e) been guilty of serious misrepresentation in providing any</p><p>information required of you under Regulation 23 of the Public Contracts Regulations 2006?</p></td><td><p>No</p></td></tr></table><p><a id=\"PART_1:_FORM_D_-_Economic_and_Financial_\"></a> PART 1: FORM D - Economic and Financial Standing\t</p><p><strong>Important Notice:</strong></p><p><strong>Where the Potential Provider is a consortium or association of suppliers, the financial information is required for each Potential Provider that is a member of the consortium or association. Where the Potential Provider is a subsidiary of a group, the financial information is required for both the subsidiary and the parent company.</strong></p><p><strong>Parent company and/or other guarantees of performance and financial standing may be required if considered appropriate by the Authority.</strong></p><table><tr><td><p><strong>2</strong></p></td><td colspan=\"4\"><p><strong>FINANCIAL INFORMATION</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2.1</p></td><td><p>What was your overall turnover in each of the last two financial years?</p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>£ 412,472.00 for year ended</p><p>31 / 03 / 2025</p></td><td><p>£ 152,013.00 for year ended</p><p>31 / 03 / 2024</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"5\"><p>2.2</p></td><td colspan=\"4\"><p>Please provide the information indicated below:-</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><em>A copy of your audited accounts for the most recent two years</em></p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>This information must be submitted</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><em>A statement of your turnover, profit &amp; loss account and cash flow for the most recent year of trading</em></p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>Not required</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><em>A statement of your cash flow forecast for the current year and a bank letter outlining the current cash and credit position</em></p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>Not Required</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><em>Alternative means of demonstrating financial status if trading for less than a year</em></p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>This information must be submitted where applicable</p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td><p>3</p></td><td><p><strong>INSURANCE</strong></p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td><p>3.1</p></td><td><p>Employer’s liability insurance is a legal requirement (except for businesses employing only the owner / close family members) and this should be at least £5 million. Please confirm that you have this in place.</p></td><td><p>yes</p></td></tr></table><p><a id=\"PART_1:_FORM_E_-_Technical_and_Professio\"></a> PART 1: FORM E - Technical and Professional Ability\t</p><h1>Important Notice:</h1><p><strong>Where the Potential Provider is a special purpose vehicle and/or not intending to be the main provider of the goods or services, the information requested should be provided in respect of the principal intended provider of the goods or services.</strong></p><table><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"><p>4</p></td><td colspan=\"4\"><p><strong>EXPERIENCE AND CONTRACT EXAMPLES</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\"><p>Please provide details of up to three contracts from either or both the public or private sector, that are relevant to the Authority’s requirement. Contracts for the supply of services should have been performed during the past three years. (The customer contact should be prepared to speak to the purchasing organisation to confirm the accuracy of the information provided below if we wish to contact them).</p></td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td><p>Contract 1</p></td><td><p>Contract 2</p></td><td><p>Contract 3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4.1</p></td><td><p>Customer Organisation (name):</p></td><td><p>Ascend Payroll</p></td><td><p>MATpad Development for Learn Sheffield </p></td><td><p>Grimsby Town?</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4.2</p></td><td><p>Customer contact name, phone number and email</p></td><td><p>Richard Rowell</p><p><a href=\"mailto:Richard@Ascend.co.uk\">Richard@Ascend.co.uk</a></p><p>0333 0000 3300</p></td><td><p>Stephen Betts, CEO, Learn Sheffield</p><p><a href=\"mailto:Stephen.betts@learnsheffield.co.uk\">Stephen.betts@learnsheffield.co.uk</a></p><p>0114 250 7417</p></td><td><p>Jack Johnson</p><p><a href=\"mailto:jack@gtfc.co.uk\">jack@gtfc.co.uk</a></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4.3</p></td><td><p>Contract start date</p><p>Contract completion date</p><p>Contract Value</p></td><td><p>2023 + ongoing</p><p>Value: £750,000</p></td><td><p>2022 + ongoing</p><p>Value: £400,000</p></td><td><p>May 2025 + ongoing</p><p>Value: £40,000</p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td><p>4.4</p></td><td><p>Brief description of contract (max 150 words) including evidence as to your technical capability in this market.</p></td><td><p><strong>Elementary Payroll Platform and Specialist Digital Resources</strong></p><p>Pixel Fusion designed and delivered the Elementary platform for Ascend Payroll, a UK</p><p>based managed payroll provider operating within highly regulated financial and payroll </p><p>administration environments. </p><p>The project involved the design, development, and deployment of a secure, cloud-native </p><p>payroll bureau management platform that combined enterprise-grade operational </p><p>capability with intuitive user experience design.</p></td><td><p><strong>Fabric-Based Digital Education Platform, Transformation Roadmap and LLM Query Interface Development</strong></p><p>MATPad is a Secure Education and Operational Management Platform designed and delivered for</p><p>the education sector to support multi-academy trust (MATs) administration, workflow management, operational reporting, and secure user access management.</p><p>MATpad is a data-driven, Azure-based SaaS platform with BI Reporting that enabled MATs and schools to unify data from multiple sources, generate insight-rich reporting, and embed governance-ready narratives across key operational areas, such as attendance, performance, behaviour, SEND, finance, and more. The SaaS Cloud-enabled platform turned fragmented systems into actionable, printable, board ready reports.</p></td><td><p><strong>Cloud Data Platform and Data Warehouse Migration</strong></p><p>Pixel Fusion partnered with Sourcefour to deliver a comprehensive digital ecosystem for Grimsby Town Football Club, providing technical architecture, platform development, deployment and ongoing support services. The engagement included delivery of the club's primary website (gtfc.co.uk), the Mariners TV subscription streaming platform and the GTFC Commercial e-commerce platform.</p><p>The solution was designed to support high volumes of concurrent users during match days, major club announcements and live streaming events, whilst maintaining performance, security and accessibility standards. Pixel Fusion was responsible for platform architecture, front-end and back-end development, cloud-hosted infrastructure, integrations, deployment processes and ongoing technical support.</p><p>The project demonstrates our technical capability in delivering secure, scalable and resilient public-facing digital platforms, including content management systems, subscription services, e-commerce solutions, API integrations, cloud infrastructure and ongoing maintenance.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><p>If you cannot provide at least one example, please briefly explain why (100 words max)</p></td></tr></table><table><tr><td><p>5</p></td><td><p><strong>STAFFING</strong></p></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><p>5.1</p></td><td><p>How many staff does your organisation (including consortia members or named sub-contractors where appropriate) employ relevant to the carrying out of services and/or delivery of goods similar to those required under this contract?</p></td><td><p>Pixel Fusion employs 17 staff whom are directly involved in the delivery of services similar to those required under this contract, comprising:</p><ul><li>Directors and Strategic Delivery Leads – 2 </li><li>Project and Product Management – 2 </li><li>UX/UI Designers – 2 </li><li>Front-End Developers – 3 </li><li>Back-End and Full Stack Developers – 4 </li><li>Data and Business Intelligence Specialists – 2 </li><li>Quality Assurance and Testing Specialists – 2 </li></ul><p>This multidisciplinary in-house team enables Pixel Fusion to provide end-to-end digital services including website support and maintenance, platform development, accessibility improvements, security management, hosting and infrastructure oversight, data and reporting solutions, user experience design and agile enhancement delivery. </p><p>The team structure provides sufficient capacity to support ongoing retained services while delivering concurrent development projects and continuous improvement initiatives.</p></td></tr></table><p><a id=\"PART_2:_FORM_F:_Project_Specific_Questio\"></a></p><p> PART 2: FORM F: Project Specific Questions\t</p><h1>Technical Capability:</h1><ul><li><ol><li>In relation to the requirement, please provide details of the technicians available to the Potential Provider to provide the services, including those involved with quality control, whether or not they are independent of the Potential Provider. Please provide details of the educational and professional qualifications of the technicians responsible for providing the services.</li></ol></li></ul><table><tr><td><p>Details about the technicians available to the Potential Provider (including educational and professional qualifications)\t</p></td><td><p>We have a multidisciplinary team of experienced digital professionals capable of delivering the full range of services required under this contract, including website development, technical support, UX/UI design, accessibility compliance, Cloud infrastructure management, data and reporting solutions, quality assurance and ongoing platform enhancement.</p><p>The delivery team comprises:</p><ul><li>Strategic Delivery Leads responsible for stakeholder engagement, governance, programme oversight and digital strategy. </li><li>Project and Product Managers responsible for agile planning, resource coordination, risk management and delivery assurance. </li><li>UX/UI Designers experienced in user-centred design, information architecture, accessibility and responsive digital experiences. </li><li>Front-End Developers specialising in modern web technologies, responsive design, accessibility implementation and performance optimisation. </li><li>Back-End and Full-Stack Developers with expertise in .NET, JavaScript frameworks, APIs, database design, cloud-native architectures and systems integration. </li><li>Data and Business Intelligence Specialists experienced in Microsoft Fabric, Power BI, reporting platforms, dashboard development and data visualisation. </li><li>Quality Assurance and Testing Specialists responsible for functional testing, accessibility testing, performance validation and release assurance. </li></ul><p>The team possesses a combination of university-level qualifications, professional technical certifications and extensive practical experience delivering digital services across public sector, education, healthcare and commercial organisations. </p><p>Relevant expertise includes agile delivery methodologies, DevOps practices, cloud platforms (including Microsoft Azure), cybersecurity principles, accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1 AA), GDPR compliance, business intelligence reporting and modern software engineering practices.</p><p>Collectively, the team has delivered complex digital platforms, reporting solutions, data services, public-facing websites and operational business systems for organisations including local authorities, multi-academy trusts, charities and commercial enterprises. This breadth of experience enables Pixel Fusion to provide both strategic consultancy and hands-on technical delivery throughout the lifecycle of digital services.</p><p>Team members hold a combination of degree-level qualifications in computing, software engineering and digital disciplines together with Microsoft, cloud and technical certifications.</p><p>We have included example technical CVs as attachments:</p><ul><li>Scott Mahoney, Senior Full Stack Engineer</li><li>Mike Corrigan, Senior Developer</li><li>James Ritchie, Senior Software Engineer</li><li>Noel Hostad, Full Stack Software Engineer</li></ul></td></tr></table><ul><li><ol><li>In relation to the requirement, please provide details of the Potential Provider’s technicians experience and knowledge of relevant processes as specified above.</li></ol></li></ul><table><tr><td><p>Potential Provider</p></td><td><p>Pixel Fusion Ltd</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Details of the technicians’ experience and knowledge of processes as specified above.</p></td><td><p> Pixel Fusion's technical team has extensive experience delivering the full lifecycle of digital services, from discovery and requirements gathering through to design, development, testing, deployment, support and continuous improvement.</p><p>Our team operates using established Agile delivery methodologies, supported by structured governance, sprint planning, backlog management, stakeholder engagement and regular review cycles. We have successfully delivered websites, data platforms, reporting solutions and business-critical applications for public sector, education, healthcare, charity and commercial organisations.</p><p>The team has significant experience in:</p><ul><li>Discovery workshops, stakeholder engagement and requirements analysis </li><li>User-centred design and UX research </li><li>Agile project delivery and iterative development </li><li>Website design, development and enhancement </li><li>Content management systems and digital platform delivery </li><li>Business intelligence, reporting and data visualisation solutions </li><li>Quality assurance, automated and manual testing </li><li>Accessibility auditing and WCAG 2.1 AA compliance </li><li>Security-by-design development practices </li><li>DevOps, release management and continuous deployment </li><li>Application support, maintenance and service improvement </li><li>Incident management, issue resolution and operational support </li></ul><p>Recent projects delivered by the team include:</p><ul><li>MATpad, a governed education data and reporting platform used by schools and multi-academy trusts (MATs)</li><li>Elementary, a Cloud-based payroll bureau management platform incorporating automation, reporting and operational workflows; and </li><li>Grimsby Town Football Club digital ecosystem, including website delivery, streaming services, e-commerce functionality and ongoing support.</li></ul><p>Through these engagements, our technicians have developed extensive experience in delivering secure, scalable and user-focused digital services while working collaboratively with client teams to ensure solutions align with organisational objectives, user needs and operational requirements.</p></td></tr></table><ul><li><ol><li>In relation to the requirement, please provide details of the Potential</li></ol></li></ul><p>Provider’s technicians experience and knowledge IT &amp; Telecommunication systems.</p><table><tr><td><p>Details of the technicians’ experience &amp; knowledge of IT &amp; Telecommunication systems.</p></td><td><p>We have included <em>several technician CVs as attachments. </em>We think they are the most relevant to your ongoing web development and online maintenance service procurement. Combined, they demonstrate strong software engineering, full-stack web development expertise, Cloud/Azure experience, API and platform development, Agile delivery, technical leadership and project management, as well as experience delivering and supporting long-term digital platforms.</p><p>These capabilities align well with IUKBC’s requirement for a retained web development partner responsible for platform development and ongoing website maintenance.</p><p>Example technicians’ experience and IT knowledge:</p><table><tr><td><p><strong>Technician</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Alignment to IUKBC Project</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mike Corrigan</p></td><td><ul><li>30+ years of software engineering, architecture and systems leadership experience.</li><li>Extensive experience leading development teams and managing complex software projects.</li><li>Experience managing Azure-hosted infrastructure and enterprise-grade systems.</li><li>Strong background in software development, databases, cloud infrastructure and operational support.</li><li>Experience delivering SaaS platforms and managing long-term product development.</li><li>Relevant leadership capability for account management, governance and client engagement expected within a retained service model.</li><li>Telecommunications experience</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scott Mahoney</p></td><td><ul><li>Full-stack development capability covering web, mobile and API development.</li><li>Strong experience with modern web technologies including PHP, Laravel, React, JavaScript, HTML and CSS.</li><li>Experience building and maintaining REST APIs and web applications.</li><li>Worked in Agile delivery environments and collaborated with developers, UX designers and stakeholders.</li><li>Experience planning software solutions from inception through delivery.</li><li>Exposure to Azure, DevOps, CI/CD and modern development practices.</li></ul></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><ul><li><ol><li>In relation to the requirement, please provide details of the Potential Provider’s proposed overall technical solution, including quality management systems in use, to the services required to be provided under the contract.</li></ol></li></ul><table><tr><td><p>Details of the Potential Provider’s proposed overall technical services support solution, including quality management systems.</p></td><td><p>Pixel Fusion proposes a flexible and scalable digital support and development service designed to provide Innovate UK Business Connect with a single partner for ongoing website maintenance, enhancement, technical support and project-based web development.</p><p>Our approach is centred on working collaboratively with the IUKBC digital team to understand project requirements, priorities, timescales and budgets, providing the technical capability required to support both day-to-day operational needs and future digital initiatives.</p><p>The proposed solution includes:</p><ul><li>Full website maintenance and support services</li><li>Security patching and vulnerability remediation</li><li>Availability monitoring and incident management</li><li>Accessibility auditing and remediation</li><li>CMS and platform enhancements</li><li>User experience and design improvements</li><li>Third-party integrations and API development</li><li>New website and digital platform development</li><li>Technical consultancy and roadmap planning</li><li>Ongoing optimisation and continuous improvement</li></ul><p>Pixel Fusion operates a Cloud-first delivery model and has extensive experience supporting and developing public-facing websites, business-critical applications, reporting platforms and digital services. Our multidisciplinary team includes project managers, UX/UI designers, front-end and back-end developers, quality assurance specialists and cloud infrastructure engineers, enabling us to provide end-to-end digital delivery and support services.</p><p><strong>Quality Management Systems</strong></p><p>Quality is embedded throughout our delivery lifecycle through a suite of established internal methodologies and governance processes, including:</p><ul><li>PF-ADM-01 Agile Delivery Methodology</li><li>PF-DEVM-01 DevOps Methodology</li><li>PF-TQA-01 Testing &amp; Quality Assurance Methodology</li><li>PF-IPT-01 Implementation Planning Framework</li><li>PF-DATM-01 DataOps Methodology (where applicable)</li></ul><p>These methodologies provide structured controls across planning, development, testing, deployment and operational support activities, ensuring consistency, transparency and continuous improvement throughout service delivery.</p><p>Our quality management processes include:</p><ul><li>Requirements definition and acceptance criteria</li><li>Sprint planning, reviews and retrospectives</li><li>Peer code reviews and technical assurance</li><li>Functional, integration and regression testing</li><li>User acceptance testing support</li><li>Accessibility testing against WCAG standards</li><li>Cross-browser and device compatibility testing</li><li>Security testing and vulnerability management</li><li>Controlled release and deployment management</li><li>Post-release monitoring and validation</li></ul><p><strong>Security, Accessibility and Governance</strong></p><p>Security, governance and accessibility are embedded throughout Pixel Fusion’s delivery lifecycle and form a core component of our technical support solution. We adopt a secure-by-design approach to development, maintenance and operational support, ensuring digital services remain resilient, compliant and protected against evolving threats.</p><p>Our security controls and delivery processes are aligned with recognised industry standards and best practice frameworks, including:</p><ul><li>ISO 27001 Information Security Management principles</li><li>Cyber Essentials Plus requirements</li><li>UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018</li><li>OWASP Secure Development practices</li><li>WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility standards</li></ul><p>We apply structured security controls throughout the software development lifecycle, including secure coding practices, peer review, access management, vulnerability management, patch management and controlled deployment processes. Regular security reviews and dependency monitoring help ensure platforms remain protected and up to date.</p><p>Operational security measures include:</p><ul><li>Multi-factor authentication and role-based access controls</li><li>Encryption of data in transit and at rest</li><li>Secure source control and deployment pipelines</li><li>Security patching and vulnerability remediation</li><li>Audit logging and monitoring</li><li>Backup, recovery and business continuity processes</li><li>Incident management and escalation procedures</li></ul><p>Accessibility is considered throughout design, development and testing activities. We undertake accessibility reviews, compliance testing and remediation activities to support continued alignment with WCAG standards and to ensure services remain accessible to all users.</p><p>Through regular governance reviews, service reporting and continuous improvement activities, Pixel Fusion works proactively to maintain secure, accessible and reliable digital services that meet organisational, regulatory and user requirements.</p><p><strong>Continuous Improvement</strong></p><p>Beyond routine support and maintenance, Pixel Fusion focuses on continuous improvement through regular stakeholder engagement, service reviews and enhancement planning. This enables IUKBC to respond quickly to changing organisational priorities, user needs and technology developments while maintaining a stable, secure and high-performing digital estate.</p><p>This combination of agile delivery, structured quality management, secure operational practices and collaborative working provides a robust technical solution capable of supporting Innovate UK Business Connect throughout the contract term.</p></td></tr></table><h1>Health and Safety:</h1><ul><li><ol><li>In relation to the requirement, please provide details of the Potential Provider’s health and safety management capability which is relevant to the goods or services purchased under the contract.</li></ol></li></ul><table><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p>Does your organisation have a written health and safety at work policy?</p></td><td><p>Yes </p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p>Does your organisation have a health and safety processes and procedures to ensure legal requirements are met?</p></td><td><p>Yes </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>If you have answered “No” to either of the above please explain why:</p></td><td colspan=\"2\"></td></tr></table><p><a id=\"SIGNATURE\"></a></p><table><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"><p><strong>7</strong></p></td><td colspan=\"2\"><p>I declare that to the best of my knowledge the answers submitted in this PQQ are correct. I understand that the information will be used in the process to assess my organisation’s suitability to be invited to tender for the Authority’s requirement and I am signing on behalf of my organisation. I understand that the Authority may reject this PQQ if there is a failure to answer all relevant questions fully or if I provide false/misleading information</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><p><strong>FORM COMPLETED BY</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7.1</p></td><td><p>Name:</p></td><td><p> Gareth Heggie, Director</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7.2</p></td><td><p>Date:</p></td><td><p>10th June 2026</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7.3</p></td><td><p>Signature:</p></td><td><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></p></td></tr></table>"
